I'll tell you, I say that
very sincerely after reading your book

00:01:05.939 --> 00:01:09.160
the other people who I know who've read your
book as well, the question that comes up

00:01:09.160 --> 00:01:11.830
about halfway through is, why in the world
did

00:01:11.830 --> 00:01:13.159
he continue?

00:01:13.159 --> 00:01:18.590
When you went through that much pain,
that much suffering, enough that it took months,

00:01:18.590 --> 00:01:23.620
even a year to recover from a journey,
but you would come back, you were relentless

00:01:23.620 --> 00:01:25.189
in your search.

00:01:25.189 --> 00:01:28.090
So just set it up really briefly for people.

00:01:28.090 --> 00:01:29.150
What made you do this?

00:01:29.150 --> 00:01:32.810
You're a professor of theology, philosophy.

00:01:32.810 --> 00:01:36.680
What made you go on this journey starting
way back when?

00:01:36.680 --> 00:01:41.811
At first, I think it was a foolish
strategy to push it as hard as I did, but

00:01:41.811 --> 00:01:44.259
I didn't
know any better at the time or I was young

00:01:44.259 --> 00:01:46.000
and stupid.

00:01:46.000 --> 00:01:49.840
But I was trained as a philosopher
of religion with a passionate desire to

00:01:49.840 --> 00:01:52.000
understand the deep structure of the universe.

00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:58.700
I had studied some of the great minds in our
Western philosophical and Eastern traditions.

00:01:58.700 --> 00:02:01.810
When I found this methodology that Stan made
available,

00:02:01.810 --> 00:02:05.970
I just decided to push it as long and as hard
as I could.

00:02:05.970 --> 00:02:09.420
And there was a great deal of suffering on
it,

00:02:09.420 --> 00:02:11.550
episodically and periodically.

00:02:11.550 --> 00:02:14.790
But at the end of every episode of intense
suffering,

00:02:14.790 --> 00:02:20.700
there would be a breakthrough into
an episode, a phase of deep ecstatic bliss

00:02:20.700 --> 00:02:24.440
and deep transpersonal encounter.

00:02:24.440 --> 00:02:32.120
And the value of those insights and that ecstasy
balanced out, more than balanced out,

00:02:32.120 --> 00:02:34.510
the transient episodes of suffering.

00:02:34.510 --> 00:02:40.260
In the beginning, when you first started
the journey, the very beginning part

00:02:40.260 --> 00:02:42.920
was what you title in the book.

00:02:42.920 --> 00:02:45.590
And it took you 20 years or so after all these
experiences to

00:02:45.590 --> 00:02:48.650
finally write this book and put it out for
the rest of us.

00:02:48.650 --> 00:02:50.659
It was called The Death of Ego.

00:02:50.659 --> 00:02:56.890
And while you were in the midst of it,
you were saying, 'What was I thinking?'

00:02:56.890 --> 00:02:59.930
So let's just set it up with what that very
first-

