and we only have about 45 minutes,
people are going to have to read the book

00:03:03.610 --> 00:03:05.980
themselves,
we're going to hopscotch through the phases

00:03:05.980 --> 00:03:07.390
you went through.

00:03:07.390 --> 00:03:09.569
But let's start with
'What was I thinking?'

00:03:09.569 --> 00:03:12.799
What happens upon the dissolution of the ego?

00:03:12.799 --> 00:03:17.110
If you want to allow your consciousness to
expand into the broader dimensions,

00:03:17.110 --> 00:03:21.239
the deeper dimensions of consciousness,
you must surrender the narrow bandwidth of

00:03:21.239 --> 00:03:23.840
your individual body,
mind, ego.

00:03:23.840 --> 00:03:28.500
And so this happens slowly or fast, convulsively
or smoothly.

00:03:28.500 --> 00:03:32.170
But that identity
that we hold has to be shattered, has to be

00:03:32.170 --> 00:03:34.319
kind of destroyed.

00:03:34.319 --> 00:03:38.860
And when it's destroyed, then
your consciousness does naturally expand-

00:03:38.860 --> 00:03:44.060
expands into a deeper register of wider spectrum
of consciousness.

00:03:44.060 --> 00:03:47.540
If you do this,
if your journey continues repeatedly, as we'll

00:03:47.540 --> 00:03:52.420
get to,
you go through many such death sequences.

00:03:52.420 --> 00:03:57.340
But it's not repeating the original ego death,
the original ego death is kind of the first

00:03:57.340 --> 00:04:04.610
transition from your time space identity into
a deeper spiritual experience of the universe.

00:04:04.610 --> 00:04:05.629
Thank you for that.

